casebody.data:
In the Matter of the Proceeding under Grade Crossing Elimination Act, for the Elimination of the Existing Highway-Railroad Crossing at Grade of the Railroad Operated by the New York Central Railroad Company, at Ridge Road in the Town of West Seneca, Erie County, New York. (Case No. 8253.)

Order affirmed, with costs. All concur. (The order denies a motion for a rehearing in a grade crossing elimination proceeding.)

Present — Sears, P. J., Crosby, Cunningham, Taylor and Dowling, JJ.
